    en: "When a safe deposit box renter dies, the bank cannot simply hand the keys to the family. SCPA Section 2003 lets an interested person petition the Surrogate's Court for an order authorizing an examination of the box to locate a will, a cemetery plot deed, or a life insurance policy. The examination happens with a bank officer present. The will is delivered to the court clerk; the burial deed goes to whoever is arranging the funeral; the life insurance policy goes to the named beneficiary. All other contents remain in the box — or are inventoried and held — until letters testamentary or letters of administration are issued."
